## Request ID / Correlation ID

```
Every incoming request gets a unique ID:
  1. Check for X-Request-ID header (forwarded from upstream proxy)
  2. If missing, generate a UUID
  3. Attach to the request context
  4. Include in EVERY log entry for that request
  5. Include in the response as X-Request-ID header
  6. Pass to downstream service calls (distributed tracing)
```

**Why:** When a user reports an error, the request ID lets you find every log entry for that exact request across all services.

