## Error Tracking

### Rules

- Use a dedicated error tracking service (Sentry, Bugsnag, Datadog, etc.)
- **Capture unhandled exceptions** automatically
- **Capture handled errors** that indicate bugs (not validation errors)
- **Include context**: user ID, request path, OS/browser, app version
- **Group by root cause** (not by surface text alone - same root cause should group into one issue regardless of variation in error messages)
- **Alert on new errors** (errors that have never been seen before)
- **Alert on error spikes** (error rate jumps significantly)
- **Assign and track** - every error in tracking must be assigned and resolved

### What to Send to Error Tracker

**Principle:** Send enough context to the error tracker to reproduce the issue, but never send sensitive data.

[REFERENCE] Typical error tracker payload configuration:

```
Send:
  - Unhandled exceptions / promise rejections
  - 500 errors from API handlers
  - Database connection failures
  - External service failures
  - Client-side crashes (JS errors, native crashes)

Don't send:
  - 400 errors (expected validation failures)
  - 401/403 errors (expected auth failures)
  - 404 errors (expected missing resources)
  - Rate limit hits (429)
```

---

## Performance Monitoring

### Key Metrics to Track

**Principle:** Track metrics that tell you whether the system is healthy and whether users are experiencing problems.

[REFERENCE] Common metric categories:

```
API:
  - Response time (p50, p95, p99)
  - Request rate (requests per second)
  - Error rate (% of 5xx responses)
  - Apdex score (% of requests under threshold)

Database:
  - Query time (p50, p95, p99)
  - Connection pool usage (% active connections)
  - Slow queries (threshold per query class - 500ms for CRUD, higher for analytics)

Infrastructure:
  - CPU usage (%)
  - Memory usage (%)
  - Disk usage (%)
  - Network I/O

Client (web/mobile):
  - Page load time / Time to Interactive
  - First Contentful Paint (FCP)
  - Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)
  - Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)
  - Crash-free rate (mobile)
```

### Alerting Thresholds

```
WARNING (investigate soon):
  - API p95 response time > 2s
  - Error rate > 1%
  - CPU > 70% for 5 minutes
  - Memory > 80%
  - Disk > 80%
  - Slow queries > 10/minute

CRITICAL (investigate immediately):
  - API p95 response time > 5s
  - Error rate > 5%
  - CPU > 90% for 2 minutes
  - Memory > 90%
  - Disk > 90%
  - Service health check failing
  - Database connection failing
  - 0 requests/sec (service might be down)
```

